    "Second Presbyterian dhurPh Will Welcome Returned Soldiers Today Members of the Second Presbyterian church Tenth avenue and Twelfth street Tho were in the army or navy during the war will be welcomed home at spe cial services today There were 32 members of this congregation who joined thi coiors the pastor the Rev Albert Grady Harris serving for several months last ear m The musical programme fjr the wel coming services at 11 oclock this morn irg is as follows Organ Homage to Baptists Rock well double quartet Te Deum in E Floyd solo by Mrs Shelby Come Ye Blessed Scott double quartet The Song the Angels Sing Wilson violin selection Obligata by Mr Steinmehl qrgan Adoration Rockwell Mrs W A Shelby will be choir leader and soprano This congregation has adopted an inno vation to call attention of the people to the church and the wisdom o fthe plan is being proved at every service by tiu increased attendance of strangers Suspended in front of the church is a large illuminated sign with the words This may be your church This sign can be seen from a distance of several blocks The Rev Mr Harris is a hard worker"
